text_elements.text: Scatter plot Energy Cost vs. Correctness

The scatter plot shows a clear trade-off between energy consumption and correctness more accurate outputs usually require more energy.

Baseline models cluster in the lower-left: low energy, low correctness.

One baseline looks better than expected, but this is misleading due to Wikipedia retrievals being somewhat relevant to the ARC-easy.

Optimized systems move toward the upper-right: higher correctness and better quality, with increased energy use.

System Analysis V1 is an outlier inefficient instructions caused high energy use but poor accuracy.
